Market Analysis and Insights

Global Oat Yoghurt Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global oat yoghurt market growing at a CAGR of 8.73% in the forecast period of 2022-2029. The rise in health consciousness globally is escalating the growth of oat yogurt market.

Oat yoghurt is a type of yoghurt made from oat milk that is a healthier alternative to regular yoghurt. Oat yoghurts are typically made with plant-based ingredients such as fruits, vegetables, and nuts. These yoghurts come in a variety of flavours, including strawberry, plain, raspberry, and chocolate.

Rapid urbanisation and the consumption of unhealthy foods have had a significant impact on health conditions. This has resulted in increased demand for oat yoghurt all over the world. The market's growth is being aided by a gradual shift toward a healthier lifestyle. Oat yoghurt have a high protein, mineral, dietary fibre, vitamin, and carbohydrate content. Oat yoghurt are also high in antioxidants, which help to protect the body from chronic diseases such as diabetes, cardiovascular disease, and cancer. Growing consumer awareness of the various benefits of oat consumption is driving market growth.

Furthermore, the rise in the working class is increasing the demand for oat yoghurt. Breakfast consumption has decreased globally as aa result of a hectic lifestyle and long work hours. Consumers are drawn to the need for a quick breakfast with nutritional value. Oat yoghurt are simple to prepare and keep for a long time. Instant oat yoghurt are also used in the preparation of cookies, breads, and muffins. The rise in obesity cases around the world is driving up demand for oat yoghurt, which lowers cholesterol levels and helps prevent obesity and overweight problems.

On the other hand, consumption trends for food products are constantly changing, and this vulnerable trend is expected to limit market growth from 2022 to 2029. The high cost of these ingredients in comparison to substitute products is also expected to challenge the market growth.

